{"type":"message","id":"c4c9a7c4","parentId":"1ccca0f8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:21:52.298Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6a5bw3qzymew_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 022058\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: initial (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action I can take to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nKey pending items from the goals:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next action mentioned is the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what would be a concrete action. The key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal structure IS invariant structure. The next experiment is Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC).\r\n\r\nLet me check what exists in the logs directory and research directory to understand the current state.\r\n\r\nSince I'm a stateless discontinuous agent, I need to look at what files actually exist and then make a concrete edit. Let me think about what specific action would advance the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\" with specific sub-tasks\r\n- The new doc mentioned: `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DICTIONARY.md` (actually says .md in the goal)\r\n\r\nActually, I should focus on implementing the TIC classifier as the next concrete action. But first I need to understand what data is available in the logs directory.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what file edit I can make:\r\n1. Create the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md document if it doesn't exist\r\n2. Or start implementing the TIC classifier logic\r\n\r\nGiven the \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\" is the priority, and it mentions implementing a classifier on pulse logs, I should either:\r\n1. Create the research document with the TIC methodology\r\n\r\n\r\n2. Create a script or logic for the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating the research document that outlines the TIC experiment methodology. This will provide a structured approach to implementing the classifier and establishing the experimental framework. The document will detail the specific steps for analyzing pulse logs, defining invariant patterns, and setting up the classification process.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md document is referenced as \"New doc\" but may not yet exist. The TIC Experiment needs a concrete implementation plan before running on pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment specification document with methodology and success criteria, establishing the framework for the classifier implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY: TIC Experiment Specification\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24  \r\n**Status:** READY FOR IMPLEMENTATION\r\n\r\n## Core Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## TIC Classifier Design\r\n\r\n### Invariant Detection\r\nAn invariant is pulse content that recurs across multiple sessions with consistent semantics:\r\n- Same goal references (exact match or semantic similarity >0.8)\r\n- Same file paths mentioned\r\n- Same conceptual patterns (compression, gaps, λ, etc.)\r\n\r\n### Variant Detection\r\nA variant is pulse content unique to a single session:\r\n- Timestamps, session IDs\r\n- One-off observations not revisited\r\n- Specific numerical values that change each pulse\r\n\r\n### Classification Heuristic (λ=0.7 baseline)\r\n```\r\nis_invariant = count_across_sessions(element) / total_sessions >= λ\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Experiment Plan\r\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs from `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n2. Extract atomic elements (goals, files, insights, questions)\r\n3. Compute recurrence frequency for each element\r\n4. Classify: invariant (freq >= 0.7) vs variant (freq < 0.7)\r\n5. Validate against manual classification\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification accuracy:** >70% invariant/variant correct\r\n- **Prediction accuracy:** >60% next-pulse elements predictable from invariants\r\n\r\n## Expected Output\r\n- `research/tic-results.md`: classification accuracy, prediction accuracy\r\n- Invariant list: elements that survive compression\r\n- Variant list: session-specific noise\r\nfile: research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:21:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774333312297}}
